    <item rdf:about='http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-mudric-6man-lcs-02.txt'>
        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-mudric-6man-lcs-02.txt</link>
        <title>"Least-Common Scope Communications", Dusan Mudric, Alexandre Petrescu</title>
        <dc:date>2020-11-14T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>This draft formulates a security problem statement.  The problem arises when a Host uses its Global Unicast Address (GUA) to communicate with another Host situated on the same link.  To address this problem, we suggest to select and use addresses of a least scope that are common.</description>
    </item>
